-- Metso Equipment Used in ‘Largest’ Biomass Gasification Facility
-- B y   L o u i s e   D o w n i n g
-- 2013-03-11T15:29:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-03-11/metso-equipment-used-in-largest-biomass-gasification-facility.html
Metso Oyj (MEO1V) , a Finnish engineering
company, said its equipment was used in the world’s largest
biomass gasification plant, started up by Vaskiluodon Voima Oy.  Metso supplied Vaskiluodon with a 140-megawatt facility
that uses organic waste to produce power, the Helsinki-based
company said today in a  statement  on its website.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Louise Downing in London at 
